<br>
I solve the argument once again hehe.  Look at my post under:<br>
<br>
ARENA<br>
Subject: Maxed My Defensive AA's, Now What AA's Make Me a Better Tank<br>
<br>
Read my post about TRUE AGGRO.  ANY attempt at any type of slow, or any type of proc from a weapon WILL still create aggro even though a higher spell has all ready hit the mob.  See my reasoning in my post mentioned above.<br>
<br>
However..be aware that you would prolly need to have that particular proc process at least twice (meaning attempts) to make up the aggro that someone all ready got by casting the higher end spell at the mob.  And yes its a good point that was brought up that a resist would create better aggro than a 'do not hold&quot; message because someone else cast a higher end spell.<br>
<br>
Example 1:<br>
Higher end Shaman Slow: Higher Aggro<br>
Warrior weapon procs a slow attempt with a willsapper: Prolly Need 4 attempts (Do not hold messages) to equal same amount of aggro that shaman slow would create. <br>
<br>
Example 2:<br>
Warrior weapon procs a successful slow with a willsapper: Prolly would need 2 proc's to equal same amount of aggro that the shaman higher slow would create.<br>
<br>
Example 3: Warrior uses a Truncheon of Doom 50% slow once and proc is a success.  This will 95% of the time hold aggro on the warrior when the shaman higher end slow hits.<br>
<br>
I have tested various weapons in groups hitting slow before the caster has and those have been my results.<br>
<br>
So the weapon with the higher slow (successful procs) ie..the Truncheon of Doom 50% the better chances you have of holding aggro when a higher slow hits.  The lower the percentage slow on your weapon on successful procs the more you will have to successfully proc to keep that aggro on you.<br>
<br>
Its simple.  In PoV if someone does not slow the mob or at least create enough aggro attempting to slow the mob before a shaman high end slow hits and shaman gets resisted when he cast his slow there is a good possibility that your shaman will die even with /shield thrown on him.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps,<br>
<br>
